2. [7 points] (2016 Final Exam Question) AW Inc. produces two variants of a particular product, P1 and P2, using two types of components, C1 and C2. P1 requires 1 unit of C1 and 2 units of C2, and is assembled in Seattle at a rate of 60 units/day. P2 requires 3 units of C1 and 1 unit of C2, and is assembled in Redding at a rate of 80 units/day. C1 and C2 are manufactured by suppliers in Chicago and Atlanta, respectively. The assembly facilities operate 360 days/year. AW Inc. outsources transportation operations to a third-party logistics (TPL) provider. The TPL provider offers trucks that can carry 3,000 units of either C1 or C2 at a cost of $3,200 per trip. The delivery lead-time from Atlanta to either Seattle or Redding is 5 days, whereas the delivery lead time from Chicago to either Seattle or Redding is 4 days. AW Inc. incurs an inventory holding cost of $0.35/unit/day for components that are stocked at the assembly plants and $0.25/unit/day for components that are in-transit from the supplier locations to the assembly plants.

a. [3 points] What are the total annual logistics costs if full truckload direct deliveries are made from the supplier plants to the assembly plants?

